title: jv16 PowerTools 2010 2.0.0.966
description:
This release contains changes to avoid Norton and McAfee Anti-Virus products from freezing 

the user's computer when installing PowerTools.

The updated version also contains the following other changes:

Safety improvement: Running the Clean and Fix my computer or File Cleaner with the safest 

scan option will no longer list any files relating to Windows, nor any DLL or other 

executable files.
Bug fix: The Status Bar of Star Menu Tool does not correctly show the number of items on the 

list.
Bug fix: The File Finder doesn't find all the possible files when performing a search based 

on a wild card search pattern such as "Foobar*".
Bug fix: The program can crash to "List index out of bounds".
This build contains updated translations to many languages and one new translation: Spanish
